caption: I came here for lunch specifically for the birria tacos, as they've had some fame online lately. They were even better than I expected and service was fantastic. Adding the fried cheese is a must! I dare you not to drink the leftover consomme. I was surprised by how the homemade pickled jalapenos and veggies were so fresh, the perfect side for the meal. I will be back soon!

This place is the most authentic I’ve tried in Chicago! Coming from Texas it’s hard finding good tasting breakfast tacos and this place has them! The corn tortillas were hand made and the flavors were amazing!! If you are looking for quality and good flavors this is it!
Foremost, fresh and cleverly presented food. Great service. Vibrant atmosphere.
This is by far not just the best Mexican restaurant but best restaurant period in ALL of Chicago. For great people watching, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday nights are the best.
DELICIOUS Food..they make from scratch..have to come back and try their other Food..😃
Breakfast burrito was great.  Added chorizo at my request. Friendly staff, ready to accommodate.  Will be back.
I love the motif here. So clever yet so homey. Makes me feel safe and comfortable.

This place is great. Doing outdoor seating due to but I didn't have any issues getting a table for brunch. We got there at 11am and was seated w/in 15 minutes. Food is always great here, definitely recommend getting their chipotle cheddar potatoes. Don't think about sharing with your significant other because you will fight over the last bite, get your own. Lattes are super delicious here, I got one every time I come.
The fish tacos are delicious! The tortillas are great along with the drinks. Try the lemonade. Can't wait until the next location opens up. Definitely coming back.

Deviled eggs were BOMB and so was the halibut. Also tried the beer sampler and they were all good just a couple that are not my preferred flavor profile. (I don't even know what that means)  Cleaned my plates and went to my hotel fat and happy.
The breakfast burritos + tacos were 5/5... The pickled jalapenos put this food in dreamland
A fav location for tasty Mexican food. the service here is above par. prices are appropriate for the quality.
Mexican food and the setting at this location is excellent. Everyone at our table was quite pleased.
Great spot for tasty mexican food. looking forward to returning with my relatives. it has a cool interior. food is like a place in baltimore i liked.

I've ordered lunch here acouple of times I've always enjoyed the food. I had a recent birthday party event for my son and wanted to try out there catering services. I rented the taco truck let me tell you its a blessing doing something like this so you can enjoy the party and don't have to cook they come to you and make the stuff on the spot. They where on time actually early and there customer service was excellent very nice and respectful from the beginning. I can't wait to use them for another event!
One of my preferred locations for tasty Mexican food. Excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. I'll return with my friends. Bring your hunger - portions are generous.

Has to have been one of the best breakfast burritos I had ever eaten, period.  Red onions ever so smoothly grace the texture of beans, lime, guacamole, cod, and some chipotle mayo.  Disappointed I was upcharged from the $8 special on those to $12 anytime burrito due to protein being fish, but had I known better I'd still strongly consider it. Medium sauces were delicious. Chips were few but fresh, and the horchata is unique and methodically made.
Burritos are unbeatable here. I wish them the best after the fire in their new location. Give these folks your business!
One of the best in town! The Birria and the Fish tacos are my favorite!
Good location for quality mexican food. good place to relax and unwind.  really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, i'll be back. it has a cool feel to it.
One of my preferred locations for delicious mexican food. This place is absolutely outstanding. There was fast and courteous service. This place has positive reviews for a reason.

Have they returned back to their original menu when they were on Taylor? Is steak still unavailable here? I visited the new location a month ago and I forgot what taco I had no choice to settle on. I think it was pork, but I did not enjoy it at all and was highly disappointed. They didn’t even use regular tortillas. I wish I took a picture, I meant to post a review then. Couldn’t even get through my meal. Waste of money.
mexican food... quality stuff. looking forward to coming back with my relatives.

Outstanding location for mexican food. It's so tasty. There was fast and courteous service.

Best tacos I have had in Chicago hands down, and I’ve been all over the city. The tortillas are made by hand right in front of you. The portions are generous and the staff is friendly and fast. Get the Pibil tacos and be ready to take a moment and collect yourself after the first bite!
Great

mexican food at this place - very good. do yourself a favor and try this place. had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. this place has a good atmosphere. makes me feel like i am back in tucson.

Let me help you decide. This place is mediocre at best. I mean if you are a real Mexican and know what mexican food taste like, then this is not for you. But if you are white and think that anything that has "mexican" on it is good. Then this is for you.

Outstanding place for tasty Mexican food. you will not be disappointed in the menu and service. next time i'll be back with my relatives. this place has a nice atmosphere. wish it was closer to my house, i would come every week.

On Tuesdays they have deals on tacos they are $2.00 each.  I tried the chicken and pork tacos. They were so good. You can taste the seasoning in the meat along with a sweet taste which I believe is mango or pineapple.  This is the prefect location for me. It took about 5 mins to walk there and 5 mins back to work.  It's street parking but it's metered parking be prepared to pay about $2.00 per hour.  This place is definitely worth coming back to. The only two negatives would be that the salsa given were spicy and I was sweating quite a bit after. Second, the chips were bit on the oily side for my taste. Otherwise the food was delish and I would have it again. I endorse this place like a lot of other people I know. Next time, I will be visiting the location to grab a couple tacos!

As for catering services I did not like how they put a limit per guest.  If I am hosting a catering event I have already made sure I ordered enough for all of my guests.  Full Disclosure!! I used Jarabe this past weekend for a big 40th birthday party. They were amazing! The tacos tasted so delicious and the staff was outstanding. I love the red taco truck which is so fun and festive. I cannot say enough good things about my experience with them and hope to use them again soon!

So please with this restaurant! They really know how to make the night special especially if you are celebrating something like we were. I went here while I was visiting Chicago, and it was the first restaurant we went to. The BEST idea ever. I love the ambiance in the dining area, suuuper cute. The server/cashier kept looking at me, which she told me she was wondering why I’m not eating- so she made sure I got my burrito right away after that. She even refilled my horchata for me which I was savouring because it’s my favourite. Customer service was great, we came before closing too! I came back the next day and got more horchata before exploring the city!  When I go back to Chicago, this will be the first place I go to again!

I had a carne asada burrito for lunch, and made the poor choice of "making it a meal" wherein rice and beans are also provided. The carne asada was fantastic; I've never had it so juicy and tender.  There was also red onion slaw in the burrito, I think made with just red onion and red cabbage, that was shockingly good (I'm usually not big on raw red onion or raw cabbage).  They're very busy, so consider takeout or delivery, but definitely put this food in your face.

I lived in SoCal for many years and have to say this was phenomenal Mexican food at great prices! The Al pastor was a bit cumin heavy for my personal tastes, but it was still fantastic. Get a couple different types of tacos, you wont regret it!
The only thing I don't like about this place is that I like their food so much , I spend too much money on steak tacos. Sooo amazing
Ordered for delivery and they gave me the wrong items or didn't include items I purchased. Called the restaurant and no one answered the phone. Won't be ordering from here again...
Great food, but they get the order wrong a lot. Be sure to double check your order. They have two different types of chicken and I always get the one I don't want
I've ordered from this place for over a year and the food and service never ceases to amaze me.

I can't recommend Jarabe enough. I wish that I could give them 10 stars. They did a catering job recently that was so great and well received by everyone that I couldn't of been happier. The food was the best ever. Delivery was on time, on point and everything as promised. Chicken, steak, sides, chips all better than expected. The only mistake was it was so great that everyone ate everything and we had no leftovers..... Alexis was accommodating, patient and made this a great experience.
free chips keeps them on par with Chillangos

Such a great experience using them! I hosted a rooftop party and thought the street food fare would be a nice touch. Great food, generous portions and they came and set up all the catering! Everyone asked me where did I get this great food from! I definitely recommend!
Great place for tacos
Good food
Tacos are hit or miss depending on your selection (I prefer the steak based ones) but the sauces are pretty good. Goes from 4 star to 5 star for the guacamole, service, and cheap prices.

Amazon food and a great staff! Make sure to grab some fish tacos when they have them and try their specials. They are constantly coming up with new things and each one is more delicious than the last!  If you're coming for lunch, don't be discouraged by the line because it's like a well oiled machine back there and my order is usually ready within 5min or so.  Much love to the hardworking Jarabe staff ❤️
Excellent Mexican food
Best Mexican food in the city. The staff is fantastic and friendly. I could eat here daily.
A secret gem I just recently found out about

Yuuuuum. Superrrr good food, quick service, and inexpensive. Just what I like. I called in my to-go order for a carne asada burrito and was told "give me 5 minutes." Wow, that is quick. Got there, paid, and was asked if I wanted any to-go sauces. Heck yes. Both please. The burrito itself was flavorful AF! The carne asada was tender and juicy, with a hint of smokiness. Loved it. My only gripe was that there wasn't any avocado :( Here I was surprised that the description had avocado without having to pay extra but nope, none was to be found in my burrito.. Maybe cause it's out of season? But "this is America and I want it now" Well, no worries, cause it was still delicious.  Excited for my lazy days of not packing a lunch so I can come back here!  Things to note: -They accept Samsung Pay!! (gotta get my points if you have a Samsung phone and don't have SP, get on it!! Message me for a referral code :D) -Taco Tuesdays! $2 tacos on Tuesday! Only a .50 cent savings but that's a whole $1 if you buy 2! -They have lengua tacos but no lengua burritos.. interesting..
Taco Tuesdays are a steal.

They're all right. They can try be more friendly. The Tacos was ok, but I've had better Tacos. I just stop there once in a while, this place was once was owned by another Taco joint. It's very small and close at 5pm.
Best sauce
Too small, need more tables. EXCELLENT FOOD... Stop by if you are in the area
Must try place.....!!!!! Awesome food. Worth it.
Our office had Jarabe cater an office lunch and everyone enjoyed the food immensely. We would absolutely order from them again. Delicious food, on time delivery and great staff.
Best Mexican food on Taylor St.!  Their carne asada is delicious.  Highly recommend if you're in the mood for Mexican food!
Excellent service great food it's a must try I will add they didn't have grilled onions but they made them for us!

(Translated by Google) Because this super delicious and all the tacos are superching very delicious mm mm mm delight 😊😋🌮🌮  (Original) Porque esta super riquísimos y todos los tacos están superchingonsisimos mm mm mm delicia 😊😋🌮🌮
Proof that great things come in small packages. Food is always fresh and seasoned perfectly. Atmosphere and customer service is warm and inviting. Gotta try the breakfast tacos.. OMGGG!

Teddy treats you right, whether you're there for hangover chilaquiles or just some tacos for lunch. Don't miss the home-made chips and guac and be sure to get a horchata coffee when you're there for brunch.
Oh man what a place. Reminds me of authentic street food culture while I was in that place. Place is usually super crowded bcos of the good food they serve there. Some of the best tacos I've ever had
Amazing mushroom tacos. Super friendly staff.

Tried the Carne Asada, the Al Pastor and the Birria. All were excellent! Been back to try the Carne Asada torta... The meat is tender and flavorful. The chips were nicely deep fried to a crispness... Quality joint!
The food is excellent. The staff is very nice. The breakfast tacos are my favorites so far, but everything is delicious. Small space, but they have great food and Dark Matter coffee.

The staff here weren't just nice, they all seemed like genuinely good people. That alone made me want to go back but the food is delicious. It's a smaller place that closes in the early evening so you may need to plan your visit or try delivery but I absolutely plan on visiting again to try more of their menu items. I recommend the birria.
Awesome tacos. Get the chips and guacamole, too.

stumbled randomly upon this fantastic little gem, made my week. Thanks Chicago for great little places like this. Steak was brillinat, egg tacos perfect.. all at the recommendation of the chef/owner/super cool cashier. Some days I hate trying to figure out what I want and nothing is worse than a restaurant that can't help you decide. This place made life good again.
Excellent tacos.  Kind of wish the Carne asada was cut into thinner slices but the meat tasted great.  Hibiscus tea was refreshing.
Never dissatisfied. Been their a few times already. Still exploring the menu choices.  P. S. Bring back the California burrito!!!

The chilaquiles Verde's for 8 bucks was a large plate with a generous helping of chorizo and two perfect, yolky, fried eggs. I was very pleased with how courteous the staff was. They were out of a few items, but such is the life of the small business.
2nd time there,  got the tacos and they where quick and delicious. Will definitely be coming back,  hope they stay,  this location has changed hands quite a few times.

In the mood for some Mexican breakfast and saw reviews and excited for this. I had the steak and egg tacos and goat. I thought the steak was good but not as flavorful as I hoped it would be. The tortilla was soggy when I got it. The goat was on point good flavor and definitely can taste the tender meat. My wife's breakfast burrito was not good she said she wouldnt go back. We got carry out so could have affected the experience.
Super disappointed I didn't realize the breakfast tacos are available all day, but the tinga was pretty good consolation.

Hands down the best restaurant in the tri-taylor area. Everything I've had on the menu is terrific. The Carne Asada tacos are my favorite. If they didn't close so early everyday I would probably end up going here more times a week than I am comfortable admitting.

Very nice staff, very nice food. Their breakfast burrito is fantastic; thanks for introducing me to arugula, guys.  Something that might be overlooked is that the salsas Jarabe offers are also very unique and delicious. They come as mild/medium/hot but each has its own unique flavor profile.
These people really set themselves apart from any other taco place. Everything on the menu is good.
the best Mexican food. every  it's cook with fresh ingredients. Simply delightful
